int i;
}

Test t = new Test();
System.out.println(t.i);
}
}

2. 0
3. compiler error
4. runtime error

4. protected

8
Predict the output of the following Java program.
class Demo
{
int a, b;
demo()
{
a = 10;
b = 20;
}
public void print()
{
System.out.print("a = " + a + " b = " + b + " ");
}
}

class Test {
public static void main(String[] args) {
demo obj1 = new demo();
demo obj2 = obj1;
obj1.a += 1;
obj1.b += 1;
obj1.print();
obj2.print();
}
}
1. Compile error
2. a = 11 b = 21 a = 11 b = 21
3. a = 11 b = 21 a = 10 b = 20
4. a = 11 b = 20 a = 10 b = 21
5. Run time error
9

1) getClass()
2) hashCode()
3) equals()
4) toString()

2. 2,3,4
3. 1,2,4
4. 1,3,4

4. constructors

   ExtraType
